1
00:00:22,331 --> 00:00:24,431
Hello, this is Haruta from Tenku Real Estate.

2
00:00:24,431 --> 00:00:25,930
[Soichi Haruta (33) | Sales Department]

3
00:00:25,930 --> 00:00:29,331
Would you like to see the apartment "Louvre Shin-musashino"? The next available appointment is...

4
00:00:29,331 --> 00:00:32,281
Our 11 o'clock appointment, Mr. Ohshima, is at the station now.
[Masamune Takekawa (44) | Sales Department Supervisor]

5
00:00:32,281 --> 00:00:33,930
Someone go get him.

6
00:00:33,930 --> 00:00:36,431
I can do that, Sir.
[Maika Segawa (45)]

7
00:00:36,431 --> 00:00:41,914
Yes! The 30 million yen apartment in Musashino-zaka is sold.
[Utamaro Kuribayashi (23)]

8
00:00:41,914 --> 00:00:45,365
It's his 5th sale this month.

9
00:00:48,930 --> 00:00:51,030
[Haruta | Kuribayashi]

10
00:00:52,173 --> 00:00:56,430
I need everyone's attention.

11
00:00:58,992 --> 00:01:02,400
Thanks to your hard work,

12
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,430
we've achieved this month's sales target.

13
00:01:04,433 --> 00:01:09,559
We are now the top-selling branch in the Kanto region.

14
00:01:09,559 --> 00:01:11,930
[Musashi Murosawa (55) | Sales Department Director]

15
00:01:12,665 --> 00:01:15,431
But we will not rest on our laurels.

16
00:01:15,442 --> 00:01:20,368
- We will continue to fight until we lead the company.
- Yes, Sir.

17
00:01:20,368 --> 00:01:22,465
Go back to work.

18
00:01:23,707 --> 00:01:26,107
- Haruta.
- Yes?

19
00:01:26,107 --> 00:01:30,265
You can handle the weekend sales campaign.

20
00:01:30,265 --> 00:01:31,830
Me? Yes!

21
00:01:31,830 --> 00:01:34,690
It's your chance to turn things around.

22
00:01:34,690 --> 00:01:36,930
I'm counting on you.

23
00:01:38,206 --> 00:01:41,165
Such a klutz.

24
00:01:42,431 --> 00:01:46,273
Sorry. I'll do it.

25
00:01:52,690 --> 00:01:56,830
Watch me. I'll lick my elbow.

26
00:01:56,830 --> 00:01:59,348
That's impossible to reach.

27
00:02:01,498 --> 00:02:04,206
Soichi Haruta, age 33. I want to fall in love!

28
00:02:04,206 --> 00:02:07,498
That's why I'll lick my elbow.

29
00:02:08,914 --> 00:02:12,381
I really like cabin attendants.

30
00:02:15,107 --> 00:02:17,014
Did I say something weird?

31
00:02:17,014 --> 00:02:21,098
They're all in the fashion business. What's wrong with you?

32
00:02:21,098 --> 00:02:23,749
- He told me you were cabin attendants.
- Be quiet.

33
00:02:23,749 --> 00:02:28,030
I also like women in fashion. I love clothes.

34
00:02:29,265 --> 00:02:32,130
Maki, you're next.

35
00:02:32,130 --> 00:02:34,582
I'm Ryota Maki.

36
00:02:34,582 --> 00:02:37,014
I worked at Tenku's headquarters as a real estate developer.

37
00:02:37,014 --> 00:02:38,723
Pleased to meet you.

38
00:02:38,723 --> 00:02:41,056
How cool!

39
00:02:43,165 --> 00:02:46,256
- Nice to meet you.
- Hello, there.

40
00:02:50,131 --> 00:02:53,014
What a wonderful restaurant.
[Choko (50) | Kurosawa's Wife]

41
00:02:53,014 --> 00:02:54,515
- Really?
- Indeed.

42
00:02:54,515 --> 00:02:57,114
I'm glad you like it.

43
00:03:00,457 --> 00:03:04,582
Last but not least, I'm Utamaro Kuribayashi. Nice to meet you.

44
00:03:04,582 --> 00:03:06,829
Go for it, Maro!

45
00:03:06,833 --> 00:03:09,359
These two guys are my colleagues.

46
00:03:09,359 --> 00:03:11,616
No, I'm your senior.

47
00:03:14,930 --> 00:03:18,498
He bombed that one. Okay, let's make a toast.

48
00:03:18,498 --> 00:03:22,265
For your information, Haruta is a mama's Boy.

49
00:03:22,265 --> 00:03:24,114
- I'm not.
- Yuck.

50
00:03:24,114 --> 00:03:26,181
Let me remind you. I'm your boss.

51
00:03:26,181 --> 00:03:28,510
You haven't had a girlfriend in five years.

52
00:03:29,540 --> 00:03:30,930
Seriously?

53
00:03:30,930 --> 00:03:34,248
I only attend these matchmaking parties,

54
00:03:34,248 --> 00:03:38,830
because I believe that I'll find the love of my life one day.

55
00:03:38,830 --> 00:03:42,470
- Cheers!
- Sure. Let's drink to that.

56
00:03:43,398 --> 00:03:45,807
Wow, delicious.

57
00:03:47,498 --> 00:03:51,149
Here we are at our 30th wedding anniversary.

58
00:03:51,149 --> 00:03:52,930
Time has gone by so fast.

59
00:03:52,930 --> 00:03:56,090
Yes, it has.

60
00:03:56,090 --> 00:04:00,138
This is slightly embarrassing for me.

61
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:02,040
For you.

62
00:04:03,665 --> 00:04:06,223
- How beautiful!
- You think?

63
00:04:06,223 --> 00:04:07,973
- What a surprise.
- That hurts.

64
00:04:07,973 --> 00:04:10,931
- I was lucky to marry you.
- You think so?

65
00:04:10,931 --> 00:04:14,431
Let's continue to get along well.

66
00:04:14,431 --> 00:04:16,431
Likewise.

67
00:04:18,306 --> 00:04:22,698
- Who wants to go karaoke?
- Let's go.

68
00:04:24,014 --> 00:04:26,640
Not you, Haruta.

69
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:30,040
Where do you think you're going?

70
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:33,431
- Taxi.
- Here we go!

71
00:04:34,431 --> 00:04:36,930
- Behave yourself.
- Ouch!

72
00:04:36,930 --> 00:04:40,014
We're young, we should walk.

73
00:04:40,014 --> 00:04:43,373
- Be quiet. Okay?
- What are you doing?

74
00:04:43,373 --> 00:04:45,830
Driver, take him home.

75
00:04:50,248 --> 00:04:53,131
Which karaoke bar?

76
00:04:53,131 --> 00:04:55,830
No wonder he has no girlfriend.

77
00:04:59,831 --> 00:05:02,830
Damn it!

78
00:05:10,790 --> 00:05:13,807
Mom, why did you do that?

79
00:05:13,807 --> 00:05:15,973
That's my line, Son.

80
00:05:15,973 --> 00:05:17,998
You're home late every night.

81
00:05:17,998 --> 00:05:21,248
Your shoes and clothes are everywhere, and you never clean up your dirty dishes.

82
00:05:21,248 --> 00:05:24,540
When I wash your pants, there are always tissues and receipts in the pockets.

83
00:05:24,540 --> 00:05:26,290
Whatever. What time is it?

84
00:05:26,290 --> 00:05:27,830
It's already past 8 a.m.

85
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:31,148
You're 33 years old, stop acting like a child.

86
00:05:31,148 --> 00:05:33,914
No time for a shower.

87
00:05:33,914 --> 00:05:36,230
- Why didn't you wake me?
- I've decided.

88
00:05:36,230 --> 00:05:38,107
- On what?
- I can't watch you ruin your life.

89
00:05:38,107 --> 00:05:40,740
- I want you to move out now.
- Why would I?

90
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:43,640
- I'm serious.
- I'll be late.

91
00:05:43,640 --> 00:05:46,020
Fine. I'll leave, then.

92
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:47,890
Do as you wish.

93
00:05:48,882 --> 00:05:52,090
- I mean it.
- Shut up!

94
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:01,410
[Press the button during night]

95
00:06:26,830 --> 00:06:28,984
Stop that!

96
00:06:32,140 --> 00:06:34,348
He fondled me.

97
00:06:34,348 --> 00:06:36,907
He assaulted me.

98
00:06:36,907 --> 00:06:40,123
You stroked my butt, didn't you?

99
00:06:40,123 --> 00:06:42,573
You're a molester. Get off the bus.

100
00:06:42,573 --> 00:06:45,498
He didn't do it.

101
00:06:45,498 --> 00:06:47,782
- Excuse me.
- Director?

102
00:06:47,782 --> 00:06:53,348
His left hand is on the strap, the right holds the bag.

103
00:06:53,348 --> 00:06:56,590
I don't think that's physically possible.

104
00:06:56,590 --> 00:07:00,730
But don't worry, we all make mistakes.

105
00:07:00,730 --> 00:07:04,556
- I'm sorry.
- No problem.

106
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:08,656
Thank you, Sir.

107
00:07:08,656 --> 00:07:10,930
I'm glad to be able to clear up the misunderstanding.

108
00:07:10,930 --> 00:07:12,981
Thank you.

109
00:07:26,854 --> 00:07:29,138
- My phone.
- I'll get it.

110
00:07:29,140 --> 00:07:31,040
Thanks.

111
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:33,650
What?

112
00:07:37,930 --> 00:07:41,056
- I'll see you at work.
- Sure.

113
00:07:53,210 --> 00:07:55,610
[Emergency Stop Button]

114
00:07:57,344 --> 00:08:01,540
Our Spring Sales Campaign starts this weekend.

115
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:03,390
What are the specific goals?

116
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:07,373
We aim to sell all five properties during the campaign.

117
00:08:07,373 --> 00:08:10,206
Haruta, are the posters and flyers ready?

118
00:08:10,206 --> 00:08:13,114
Oh, yes. I've started delivering them.

119
00:08:13,114 --> 00:08:14,830
Are there any customer complaints?

120
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:19,306
Kuribayashi took a customer to view a property,

121
00:08:19,306 --> 00:08:22,390
but he got lost and couldn't find it.

122
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:24,330
How did that happen, Maro?

123
00:08:24,330 --> 00:08:28,430
Haruta gave me the wrong map.

124
00:08:28,430 --> 00:08:30,830
How is that my fault? You should've checked it yourself.

125
00:08:30,830 --> 00:08:33,348
Seriously? It's your fault.

126
00:08:33,348 --> 00:08:34,930
Why are you shifting the blame on me?

127
00:08:34,930 --> 00:08:37,965
- It was your mistake.
- Why are you angry?

128
00:08:37,965 --> 00:08:41,081
Enough! Young employees quit when they're yelled at.

129
00:08:41,081 --> 00:08:43,749
- But he yelled at me first.
- I will quit.

130
00:08:43,749 --> 00:08:45,714
- What?
- I'm serious about quitting.

131
00:08:45,714 --> 00:08:50,982
Hello. You're here? Come on up.

132
00:08:50,982 --> 00:08:53,431
There he is.

133
00:09:08,707 --> 00:09:10,682
Let me introduce our newest team member.

134
00:09:10,682 --> 00:09:15,223
This is Maki, he was transferred from the headquarters' Planning Department.

135
00:09:15,223 --> 00:09:16,665
I'm Ryota Maki.

136
00:09:16,665 --> 00:09:21,998
I'm new to sales, so please give me your guidance. I'll do my best.

137
00:09:22,930 --> 00:09:24,665
[Ryota Maki (25)]

138
00:09:24,665 --> 00:09:29,723
After only three years, Maki supervised the Toyosu Renewal Project.

139
00:09:29,723 --> 00:09:31,830
He's an ace of our company.

140
00:09:31,830 --> 00:09:34,306
- Don't let him outsell you.
- Okay.

141
00:09:34,306 --> 00:09:35,565
Pleased to meet you.

142
00:09:35,565 --> 00:09:38,080
Okay, back to work.

143
00:09:38,765 --> 00:09:41,631
- It's you!
- Haruta.

144
00:09:41,631 --> 00:09:45,698
Ask him if you have any questions. He's very helpful.

145
00:09:46,940 --> 00:09:51,306
Go get the Spring Campaign data off my computer for him.

146
00:09:51,306 --> 00:09:54,130
- Yes, Sir.
- Thanks.

147
00:09:54,130 --> 00:09:57,150
Hello? Oh, sorry.

148
00:09:58,206 --> 00:10:00,165
Okay then.

149
00:10:00,165 --> 00:10:06,530
Spring Campaign... Campaign.

150
00:10:06,530 --> 00:10:09,956
Spring... Is this it?

151
00:10:14,290 --> 00:10:15,750
What the...

152
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:20,707
What are these?

153
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,560
What?

154
00:10:30,990 --> 00:10:32,730
You've got to be kidding me.

155
00:10:46,973 --> 00:10:50,415
Why does he have photos of me?

156
00:10:50,415 --> 00:10:53,665
What? Is this a dream?

157
00:10:53,665 --> 00:10:56,156
Am I dreaming?

158
00:10:59,214 --> 00:11:01,314
[Be Brave, Step Forward]

159
00:11:02,598 --> 00:11:04,249
Did you see them?

160
00:11:06,799 --> 00:11:09,430
No, I didn't.

161
00:11:11,290 --> 00:11:13,823
Are you sure?
[Be Brave, Step Forward]

162
00:11:15,098 --> 00:11:17,048
I didn't see them.

163
00:11:19,623 --> 00:11:21,530
You didn't see what?

164
00:11:24,765 --> 00:11:28,040
Not sure, but I didn't see them.
[Be Brave, Step Forward]

165
00:11:29,515 --> 00:11:31,082
I see.

166
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:34,782
It's fine if you didn't.

167
00:11:36,098 --> 00:11:37,698
[Be Brave, Step Forward]

168
00:11:45,730 --> 00:11:47,331
Dear God.

169
00:11:47,331 --> 00:11:52,930
He's not what I had in mind for the love of my life.

170
00:11:52,930 --> 00:11:59,807
[Ossan's Love]

171
00:12:00,530 --> 00:12:06,140
Firstly, some apartment buildings don't allow flyers.
[Episode 1 | Open the Door!]

172
00:12:06,140 --> 00:12:08,973
Always ask the building supervisor first.

173
00:12:08,973 --> 00:12:12,482
This is the most difficult part.

174
00:12:12,482 --> 00:12:15,682
Slipping them in gently, without folding the flyer.

175
00:12:15,682 --> 00:12:17,390
Yes, gently.

176
00:12:18,223 --> 00:12:20,498
Here, try it.

177
00:12:25,473 --> 00:12:27,540
- Hello there, Mr. Haruta.
- Gently.

178
00:12:27,540 --> 00:12:29,656
Hello!

179
00:12:29,656 --> 00:12:31,498
Ms. Morisaki, the building manager.

180
00:12:31,498 --> 00:12:32,898
I'm Maki.

181
00:12:32,898 --> 00:12:35,148
How do you do?

182
00:12:35,148 --> 00:12:38,331
Excellent timing. I have the perfect candidate.

183
00:12:38,331 --> 00:12:40,749
Another blind date? No, I'm good.

184
00:12:40,749 --> 00:12:42,930
You're not getting any younger.

185
00:12:42,930 --> 00:12:47,598
She's definitely your type. She's big, really big.

186
00:12:47,598 --> 00:12:52,306
Ma'am, what I meant was that I like big boobs.

187
00:12:52,306 --> 00:12:55,290
Don't be picky. The bigger, the better.

188
00:12:55,290 --> 00:13:00,290
Do you mean the size doesn't matter? You got it all wrong.

189
00:13:00,290 --> 00:13:03,140
- Hello.
- Hi there. See you.

190
00:13:03,140 --> 00:13:04,415
Good day.

191
00:13:04,415 --> 00:13:05,830
Hello, Haruta.

192
00:13:05,830 --> 00:13:08,830
Are you taking a walk?

193
00:13:11,014 --> 00:13:14,623
We are at the same company, but my job content is completely different.

194
00:13:14,623 --> 00:13:20,830
Yes, in the Sales Department, you really have to enjoy dealing with people.

195
00:13:20,830 --> 00:13:22,638
I'm not that great at it.

196
00:13:22,640 --> 00:13:25,073
Haruta, you're impressive.

197
00:13:25,073 --> 00:13:27,973
Is this sarcasm? I have the worst sales record.

198
00:13:27,973 --> 00:13:29,623
Not at all.

199
00:13:33,098 --> 00:13:37,231
- Hello.
- Haruta, go over to the Old Mansion right away.

200
00:13:37,231 --> 00:13:39,273
Isn't Kuribayashi handling that deal?

201
00:13:39,273 --> 00:13:42,973
I can't make sense of what he says. You go handle it.

202
00:13:42,975 --> 00:13:45,242
What? But...

203
00:13:45,830 --> 00:13:47,530
What?

204
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:49,581
Kuribayashi's screwed up again.

205
00:13:49,581 --> 00:13:53,165
Sorry, I have to go. I'll leave the rest to you.

206
00:13:53,165 --> 00:13:57,115
Just call it a day whenever.

207
00:13:57,115 --> 00:13:59,265
Good luck.

208
00:14:03,370 --> 00:14:04,830
We're terribly sorry.

209
00:14:04,830 --> 00:14:07,630
He's been so rude.

210
00:14:07,630 --> 00:14:09,830
The technician is on his way here now.

211
00:14:09,830 --> 00:14:13,440
How many times have I asked you?

212
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,830
E-Excuse me.

213
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,656
- You see?
- Put it away!

214
00:14:18,656 --> 00:14:20,857
- We're really sorry.
- This is unacceptable.

215
00:14:20,857 --> 00:14:23,482
I'll teach him a good lesson to change his perspective on life!

216
00:14:23,482 --> 00:14:25,482
- Is that clear?
- Yes, Sir.

217
00:14:28,014 --> 00:14:31,929
He's absolutely hopeless.

218
00:14:31,931 --> 00:14:34,698
I left my computer on.

219
00:14:38,973 --> 00:14:41,073
[Daily Sales Reports | Soichi Haruta]

220
00:14:44,382 --> 00:14:46,765
Oh? What's this?

221
00:14:46,765 --> 00:14:50,150
He's never left any comments before.

222
00:14:50,150 --> 00:14:52,980
[Thank you for your hard work...]

223
00:15:00,014 --> 00:15:02,573
Why only me?

224
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:27,181
You did a good job with that complainant.

225
00:15:27,181 --> 00:15:29,930
Thank you.

226
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:41,507
He always leaves on time. Why's he still here?

227
00:15:41,507 --> 00:15:45,690
Don't tell me... he's been waiting for me.

228
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:56,315
Why is he shutting the blinds?

229
00:15:58,140 --> 00:16:02,223
Why the hell is he undressing? Why did he take his jacket off?

230
00:16:03,740 --> 00:16:07,206
Hypothetically speaking, has he fallen in love with me?

231
00:16:07,206 --> 00:16:11,930
No, that can't be true. But what if it is?

232
00:16:11,930 --> 00:16:15,731
How does a junior employee deal with this?

233
00:16:21,290 --> 00:16:23,830
Calm down. You've got it all wrong.

234
00:16:23,830 --> 00:16:27,640
Haruta, you think too much.

235
00:16:30,580 --> 00:16:32,530
[Real Estate Database]

236
00:16:32,530 --> 00:16:36,322
The computer froze on me.

237
00:16:36,322 --> 00:16:38,230
Why now?

238
00:16:40,348 --> 00:16:41,830
Haruta.

239
00:16:41,830 --> 00:16:43,330
Sir...

240
00:16:44,690 --> 00:16:47,090
- If you'll excuse me.
- Haruta?

241
00:16:50,170 --> 00:16:52,565
It's all right. Calm down.

242
00:16:52,565 --> 00:16:56,482
Director doesn't have feelings for me. There's no way.

243
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:02,200
Haruta?

244
00:17:02,210 --> 00:17:05,210
[Work Life Service Shop]

245
00:17:05,210 --> 00:17:07,365
Yes, Director?

246
00:17:07,365 --> 00:17:09,390
Haruta!

247
00:17:10,181 --> 00:17:12,756
Director... what is it?

248
00:17:12,756 --> 00:17:14,040
Haruta!

249
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:15,630
I can't do this.

250
00:17:16,890 --> 00:17:20,830
No, wait! Open, open.

251
00:17:22,850 --> 00:17:24,380
Haruta?

252
00:17:25,860 --> 00:17:27,450
Haruta!

253
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:31,660
- Haruta!
- Come on, close.

254
00:17:42,973 --> 00:17:46,923
There's a cleaning tag on your collar.

255
00:17:46,930 --> 00:17:48,656
From Kurosawa.

256
00:17:52,930 --> 00:17:55,140
Damn it!

257
00:17:55,140 --> 00:17:57,693
I'm home.

258
00:17:58,393 --> 00:18:00,526
I'm back.

259
00:18:01,085 --> 00:18:02,927
Mom?

260
00:18:04,018 --> 00:18:05,827
Mom!

261
00:18:12,160 --> 00:18:16,701
Ataru and I are opening an import goods shop. Mom.

262
00:18:16,701 --> 00:18:18,867
Who the heck is Ataru?

263
00:18:28,460 --> 00:18:31,135
Where's the toilet paper?

264
00:18:35,601 --> 00:18:38,301
Where's the detergent?

265
00:18:38,301 --> 00:18:39,335
Shampoo?

266
00:18:39,335 --> 00:18:41,435
Is this it?

267
00:18:43,018 --> 00:18:45,543
There's nothing here.

268
00:18:47,227 --> 00:18:50,026
[Japanese Cuisine | Pub Wonderful]

269
00:18:50,026 --> 00:18:51,393
Your mother left home?

270
00:18:51,393 --> 00:18:54,500
Yes. Some young stud must be scamming her.

271
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:58,494
A 33-year-old living with his mom is never in favor with ladies.

272
00:18:58,494 --> 00:19:00,375
It's about time for you to live independently.
[Chizu Arai (27) | Haruta's Childhood Friend]

273
00:19:00,375 --> 00:19:03,600
You're the one to talk, Chizu. You're jobless.

274
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:06,493
I'm searching for my next job.

275
00:19:06,493 --> 00:19:07,810
By the way, why did you quit?

276
00:19:07,810 --> 00:19:12,372
I punched a guy who fondled me. One of our biggest clients.

277
00:19:12,372 --> 00:19:15,561
- So you got fired?
- No, I quit.

278
00:19:15,561 --> 00:19:18,356
My boss insisted that I apologize.

279
00:19:18,356 --> 00:19:21,791
But why should I?

280
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:23,935
It must be tough having such a feisty sister, right?

281
00:19:23,935 --> 00:19:25,285
Tell me about it.

282
00:19:25,285 --> 00:19:27,152
I wish someone would marry her.
[Teppei Arai (38) | Chizu's Older Brother]

283
00:19:27,152 --> 00:19:29,400
You can't get rid of me, you idiot.

284
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:31,460
Don't call me an idiot.

285
00:19:31,460 --> 00:19:33,018
How about marrying me?

286
00:19:33,018 --> 00:19:36,826
No, thanks. That'll mean more housework.

287
00:19:36,826 --> 00:19:38,426
That's the reason?

288
00:19:38,426 --> 00:19:42,076
I want to marry a handsome man, like a butler.

289
00:19:42,076 --> 00:19:43,310
- A butler?
- Yes.

290
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:45,600
Someone who'll do all the housework.

291
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:49,935
When I get home from work, he'll take care of me.

292
00:19:49,935 --> 00:19:51,551
- Fried udon noodles with fish roe.
- You're not listening.

293
00:19:51,551 --> 00:19:53,487
Sorry, I'm done serving food.

294
00:19:53,487 --> 00:19:55,584
- That's way too early!
- No more food.

295
00:19:55,584 --> 00:20:00,200
- Why?
- Because I'm done. Don't question me.

296
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:02,260
Go home already.

297
00:20:03,169 --> 00:20:06,784
- We're out of food.
- Don't kick me out.

298
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:12,768
Maki?

299
00:20:13,410 --> 00:20:16,219
- Haruta.
- Hey!

300
00:20:17,510 --> 00:20:19,935
You've been delivering the flyers all this time?

301
00:20:19,935 --> 00:20:22,435
Yes, I was determined to finish them today.

302
00:20:22,435 --> 00:20:24,120
What a hard worker.

303
00:20:24,120 --> 00:20:27,730
You didn't have to finish them today. I'm sorry.

304
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:30,600
No, I'm new at it. It took forever.

305
00:20:33,550 --> 00:20:35,310
Do you live nearby?

306
00:20:35,310 --> 00:20:37,600
I'm living in a weekly rental apartment.

307
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,810
When I worked at the headquarters, I was able to commute from home.

308
00:20:39,810 --> 00:20:41,700
I see.

309
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:47,051
I've been looking for a cheap place near work, but no luck so far.

310
00:20:51,860 --> 00:20:55,068
- Do you cook?
- Yes, simple stuff.

311
00:20:55,068 --> 00:20:56,935
I'm cooking fried chicken tonight.

312
00:20:56,935 --> 00:21:00,600
That's great. Frying is a real skill.

313
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:04,660
It's nothing special. I'm going that way. Good night.

314
00:21:04,660 --> 00:21:06,301
Good night.

315
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:13,407
Maki.

316
00:21:15,970 --> 00:21:19,810
Look, how about you move in with me?

317
00:21:19,810 --> 00:21:21,420
Excuse me?

318
00:21:21,420 --> 00:21:26,770
I'm at my mom's place. She's moved out, so there are spare rooms.

319
00:21:26,770 --> 00:21:29,400
It's called "room sharing".

320
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:34,226
This is rather sudden. Wait, do you want to eat my fried chicken?

321
00:21:34,226 --> 00:21:38,435
You got me. Just think about it.

322
00:21:39,290 --> 00:21:42,352
I will. Good night.

323
00:21:42,352 --> 00:21:43,952
Good night.

324
00:21:45,910 --> 00:21:49,760
The casual suggestion

325
00:21:49,760 --> 00:21:55,010
will bring dramatic changes to my life later.

326
00:21:56,500 --> 00:22:01,143
A few days later, Ryota Maki moved in with me.

327
00:22:01,143 --> 00:22:03,500
- Where should we put them?
- To my room for now.

328
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:06,545
After Maki settled in,

329
00:22:07,350 --> 00:22:11,201
I realized he's super efficient around the house.

330
00:22:13,160 --> 00:22:15,610
You left tissues in your pocket.

331
00:22:15,610 --> 00:22:17,120
Sorry.

332
00:22:18,360 --> 00:22:21,768
You're so messy. What are you, a kid?

333
00:22:21,768 --> 00:22:23,600
Sorry about that.

334
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:25,490
Not on the floor!

335
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:29,277
What a feast!

336
00:22:29,277 --> 00:22:32,135
Calories and nutrition balance are taken into consideration.

337
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,400
Go ahead.

338
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:37,400
Thank you for the food.

339
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:44,000
What in the world? It's so delicious!

340
00:22:47,010 --> 00:22:50,377
Two guys living together in a careless life.

341
00:22:50,377 --> 00:22:54,600
My lifestyle improved by leaps and bounds.

342
00:22:54,600 --> 00:23:00,600
How about we pay halves and buy a virtual reality system?

343
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,419
- What?
- VR.

344
00:23:02,419 --> 00:23:04,951
Fine, but are you into games?

345
00:23:04,951 --> 00:23:09,227
Yes, sure. And VR is brilliant when it comes to porn.

346
00:23:09,227 --> 00:23:13,198
- So that's what you're after. Not for me.
- Why not?

347
00:23:13,198 --> 00:23:15,268
I don't need it.

348
00:23:15,268 --> 00:23:17,410
Why should I pay half?

349
00:23:24,230 --> 00:23:28,442
I saw the Director with his wife the other day.

350
00:23:28,442 --> 00:23:30,584
The Director and his wife?

351
00:23:30,584 --> 00:23:33,867
Yes, all lovey-dovey, walking arm-in-arm.

352
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:44,800
Yes, of course.

353
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:47,810
That's right. He's a married man.

354
00:23:47,810 --> 00:23:52,200
She's quite pretty. I mean, she's not bad.

355
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,401
- Welcome!
- Come on in.

356
00:23:54,401 --> 00:23:57,600
I came after seeing the flyer.

357
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:59,868
Great. You have a good eye.

358
00:23:59,868 --> 00:24:04,143
Silly me. It was my misunderstanding after all.

359
00:24:04,143 --> 00:24:08,868
I was rude to the Director. I'm too self-absorbed.

360
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:14,600
Meet me at Oba Beach Park at 7 p.m. tonight. Kurosawa.

361
00:24:15,150 --> 00:24:16,680
What?

362
00:24:23,780 --> 00:24:28,343
All I can see are courting couples.

363
00:24:28,343 --> 00:24:31,600
Where's the Director?

364
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,200
I see him.

365
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:39,384
Director? What?

366
00:24:39,384 --> 00:24:41,243
What's he carrying?

367
00:24:43,290 --> 00:24:45,568
Roses?

368
00:24:48,220 --> 00:24:50,935
Good evening, Sir.

369
00:24:50,935 --> 00:24:52,826
Hello.

370
00:24:52,826 --> 00:24:55,993
Sorry to call you out here. No problems with leaving work?

371
00:24:55,993 --> 00:24:58,542
I've finished today's tasks.

372
00:24:58,542 --> 00:25:01,530
I'm relying on you for the campaign this weekend.

373
00:25:01,530 --> 00:25:05,160
Yes, I've been making preparations for that.

374
00:25:05,160 --> 00:25:07,800
Takekawa will be running the operation.

375
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:10,300
I'm in love.

376
00:25:10,300 --> 00:25:11,743
What?

377
00:25:14,310 --> 00:25:19,135
I'm in love with you, Haru-tan!
(T/N: suffix used for very cute people)

378
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:25,868
In truth...

379
00:25:25,868 --> 00:25:30,500
I intended to bury my love deep in my heart forever.

380
00:25:31,330 --> 00:25:33,435
But then...

381
00:25:33,435 --> 00:25:36,043
you saw the photos, didn't you?

382
00:25:37,140 --> 00:25:41,051
I know you saw my photos of you.

383
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:46,477
- I did.
- So now...

384
00:25:46,477 --> 00:25:50,227
I can no longer lie to myself.

385
00:25:54,600 --> 00:25:57,568
No, don't do that! Don't bow, Director.

386
00:25:57,568 --> 00:26:00,550
Raise your head, please.

387
00:26:01,168 --> 00:26:03,210
Haru-tan.

388
00:26:03,990 --> 00:26:08,800
I'm a married man. I have a wife.

389
00:26:09,700 --> 00:26:12,600
Yes, I do know that.

390
00:26:12,600 --> 00:26:16,780
So... I'll settle the matter with my wife,

391
00:26:16,780 --> 00:26:19,000
thus wait for me.

392
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:21,610
- Say what?
- Listen, Haruta.

393
00:26:22,200 --> 00:26:24,001
I'm begging you...

394
00:26:25,060 --> 00:26:27,200
give me time.

395
00:26:29,370 --> 00:26:31,300
Thank you.

396
00:26:36,710 --> 00:26:39,835
Director? Director?

397
00:26:39,835 --> 00:26:42,293
What did he thank me for?

398
00:26:42,293 --> 00:26:46,393
Don't settle anything with your wife.

399
00:26:48,310 --> 00:26:50,001
A love confession?

400
00:26:50,001 --> 00:26:51,643
Lucky you.

401
00:26:51,643 --> 00:26:53,743
Were you listening to me?

402
00:26:53,743 --> 00:26:55,943
He's a middle-aged man and he is my boss.

403
00:26:55,943 --> 00:26:58,800
No one's confessed their love to you for ages.

404
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:00,400
Wait...

405
00:27:01,360 --> 00:27:03,484
I can't recall.

406
00:27:03,484 --> 00:27:06,119
There hasn't been anybody since 5th grade.

407
00:27:07,220 --> 00:27:10,468
Just be thankful that someone loves you.

408
00:27:10,468 --> 00:27:12,143
It's like a miracle.

409
00:27:12,143 --> 00:27:15,277
Don't be stupid. He's my boss, the Director.

410
00:27:15,277 --> 00:27:17,910
You're not a big fan of office romance, or is it because he's older?

411
00:27:17,910 --> 00:27:20,600
Because he's a guy. And stop making fun of me.

412
00:27:20,600 --> 00:27:24,352
Gender doesn't matter when it comes to love─

413
00:27:24,352 --> 00:27:25,935
- It certainly is.
- No.

414
00:27:25,935 --> 00:27:30,160
Do you hate your boss?

415
00:27:32,050 --> 00:27:35,409
I respect him as a boss.

416
00:27:35,409 --> 00:27:38,843
He takes good care of his subordinates.

417
00:27:40,010 --> 00:27:41,851
As a person, I quite like him.

418
00:27:41,851 --> 00:27:43,319
Then there's no problem.

419
00:27:43,319 --> 00:27:45,500
How can you say that? Listen...

420
00:27:45,500 --> 00:27:47,493
Look, Haruta.

421
00:27:52,790 --> 00:27:58,200
I'm rooting for you and your boss.

422
00:27:58,200 --> 00:28:02,849
I don't understand you. Seriously.

423
00:28:02,849 --> 00:28:05,200
- Go for it!
- No way!

424
00:28:05,200 --> 00:28:09,643
Hey, Maki. I'm home.

425
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:13,360
Sorry about that. And nice to meet you.

426
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:15,500
I'm Chizu Arai, Haruta's childhood friend.

427
00:28:15,500 --> 00:28:18,293
Hi, I'm Maki.

428
00:28:18,293 --> 00:28:20,368
She's madly in love with me.

429
00:28:20,368 --> 00:28:23,143
Says who? Shut-up, stupid.

430
00:28:23,143 --> 00:28:25,635
He was courted by someone he doesn't like.

431
00:28:25,635 --> 00:28:26,976
Be quiet.

432
00:28:26,976 --> 00:28:30,168
He's perplexed because he was courted by someone he doesn't like.

433
00:28:30,168 --> 00:28:31,435
What's the meaning of this?

434
00:28:31,435 --> 00:28:35,835
Sorry, I have to go. He's all yours.

435
00:28:35,835 --> 00:28:39,726
- Good night.
- Are you leaving already?

436
00:28:39,726 --> 00:28:43,040
Geez, where are you taking me?

437
00:28:43,040 --> 00:28:45,430
Stay here for now.

438
00:28:47,130 --> 00:28:50,700
Don't fall asleep there.

439
00:28:50,700 --> 00:28:53,751
- Maki, get my bag.
- Hey!

440
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:56,610
My bag.

441
00:28:56,610 --> 00:29:00,500
Can you guess...

442
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,800
what do I have here?

443
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:05,585
For you.

444
00:29:05,585 --> 00:29:06,868
What is this?

445
00:29:06,868 --> 00:29:10,327
It's a present for you.

446
00:29:10,327 --> 00:29:12,993
[Haruta's Secret Sales Guide]

447
00:29:15,810 --> 00:29:18,030
[The Sales Area for the Tokyo Sales Department 2]

448
00:29:20,470 --> 00:29:22,964
[His wife's opinions matter. Get through to his wife.]

449
00:29:23,930 --> 00:29:25,789
[He loves to work out. Give him information about gyms nearby.]

450
00:29:25,789 --> 00:29:27,884
[Only the Chosen One Can Deliver Flyers. Deliver the flyers with heart.]

451
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:31,300
You made it for me?

452
00:29:43,101 --> 00:29:44,168
Good morning.

453
00:29:44,168 --> 00:29:46,300
Haruta is here.

454
00:29:46,300 --> 00:29:47,400
Morning...

455
00:29:47,400 --> 00:29:49,076
- Haruta.
- Yes?

456
00:29:49,076 --> 00:29:53,068
You put the wrong map on the campaign flyers.

457
00:29:54,010 --> 00:29:56,460
How long have you been here? Get real!

458
00:29:56,460 --> 00:30:00,000
I should have re-checked them. I'm sorry.

459
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,826
Apologies are meaningless.

460
00:30:01,826 --> 00:30:06,201
Put a correction sticker on all of them and retrieve those that went out.

461
00:30:06,201 --> 00:30:11,070
- Yes.
- We should be preparing for the campaign at 1 p.m. today.

462
00:30:11,070 --> 00:30:13,668
We're understaffed.

463
00:30:13,668 --> 00:30:17,743
Haruta has thrown us under the bus again.

464
00:30:19,976 --> 00:30:24,700
It's not the time to look at your shoes!

465
00:30:24,700 --> 00:30:27,701
Takekawa and Maki, go prepare the onsite setup.

466
00:30:27,701 --> 00:30:30,626
Segawa and Kuribahashi, go retrieve the posters near the station.

467
00:30:30,626 --> 00:30:32,784
Let's do what we can.

468
00:30:32,784 --> 00:30:34,500
You guys, get moving.

469
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:36,635
So sorry, everyone.

470
00:30:38,893 --> 00:30:43,101
Bummer! It was all my fault.

471
00:30:47,826 --> 00:30:51,360
Hang on. There are only the two of us here?

472
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:58,601
Don't tell me it's his strategy to be alone with me.

473
00:30:58,601 --> 00:31:03,426
No, focus on work. He was covering for me.

474
00:31:03,426 --> 00:31:05,727
Get me the corrected paste-overs.

475
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:12,760
Haruta?

476
00:31:18,743 --> 00:31:20,243
Director?

477
00:31:21,826 --> 00:31:24,252
I can do this by myself.

478
00:31:40,643 --> 00:31:43,093
[Real Estate Campaign]

479
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:49,043
Haruta, here! Hurry!

480
00:31:49,043 --> 00:31:50,360
I made it!

481
00:31:50,360 --> 00:31:53,150
- I made it.
- Put this on.

482
00:31:53,150 --> 00:31:55,500
No, the head goes last.

483
00:31:55,500 --> 00:31:57,586
This first.

484
00:31:59,060 --> 00:32:00,500
Now way can we finish in time.

485
00:32:00,500 --> 00:32:02,093
We still have to try.

486
00:32:02,093 --> 00:32:04,252
- It's all Haruta's fault.
- Calm down, you two.

487
00:32:04,252 --> 00:32:07,400
Don't butt in. Let me talk to him alone.

488
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:09,343
Listen, Kuribayashi.

489
00:32:11,600 --> 00:32:15,751
Put yourself in his shoes.

490
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:21,493
Would Haruta blame you if you messed it up?

491
00:32:21,493 --> 00:32:23,089
I don't think so, Sir.

492
00:32:23,089 --> 00:32:25,275
- Exactly.
- Yes.

493
00:32:25,275 --> 00:32:27,076
Now listen up.

494
00:32:27,076 --> 00:32:31,529
Success or failure will be determined at the very end.

495
00:32:31,529 --> 00:32:36,876
We won't let this simple mistake ruin our success.

496
00:32:36,876 --> 00:32:38,990
- Let's do this.
- Okay.

497
00:32:38,990 --> 00:32:40,407
For our success!

498
00:32:40,407 --> 00:32:42,644
- Let's get started!
- Yes, Sir!

499
00:32:43,868 --> 00:32:45,800
Director...

500
00:32:47,626 --> 00:32:49,226
- Haruta.
- Yes?

501
00:32:50,095 --> 00:32:51,807
It's nothing.

502
00:32:51,807 --> 00:32:53,734
Come on, let's go.

503
00:32:58,110 --> 00:32:59,650
What?

504
00:33:06,777 --> 00:33:08,577
Director!

505
00:33:10,120 --> 00:33:12,900
Director!

506
00:33:22,166 --> 00:33:23,875
Haruta?

507
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:29,690
Haruta...

508
00:33:30,470 --> 00:33:32,520
Haruta!

509
00:33:32,520 --> 00:33:34,430
Haruta!

510
00:33:34,430 --> 00:33:37,530
- Haruta!
- Haruta.

511
00:33:37,630 --> 00:33:39,235
[Ganryu General Hospital]

512
00:33:39,235 --> 00:33:42,418
He's still being treated.

513
00:33:42,418 --> 00:33:45,259
I'll call you as soon as I know his condition.

514
00:33:45,990 --> 00:33:47,510
Okay.

515
00:33:49,290 --> 00:33:50,840
Bye.

516
00:33:54,755 --> 00:33:57,330
What have I done?

517
00:33:57,330 --> 00:33:59,449
Haruta...

518
00:33:59,449 --> 00:34:01,378
It's all my fault.

519
00:34:01,378 --> 00:34:02,982
Director.

520
00:34:02,982 --> 00:34:06,400
He sacrificed himself to save me.

521
00:34:07,643 --> 00:34:09,434
Poor Haruta!

522
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:23,143
So young, how sad.

523
00:34:23,143 --> 00:34:24,267
Poor fellow.

524
00:34:24,267 --> 00:34:25,570
Indeed.

525
00:34:25,570 --> 00:34:28,596
Doctor, how is Haruta?

526
00:34:28,596 --> 00:34:29,732
Please tell me.

527
00:34:29,732 --> 00:34:32,449
